<item>
            <title>[FLINK-22525] The zone id in exception message should be GMT+08:00 instead of GMT+8:00</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-22525</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Flink SQL&amp;gt; SET table.local-time-zone=UTC+3;
Flink SQL&amp;gt; select current_row_timestamp();
[ERROR] Could not execute SQL statement. Reason:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: The supported Zone ID is either a full name such as &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;America/Los_Angeles&apos;&lt;/span&gt;, or a custom timezone id such as &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;GMT-8:00&apos;&lt;/span&gt;, but configured Zone ID is &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;UTC+3&apos;&lt;/span&gt;.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The valid zoned should&#160; be &apos;GMT-08:00&apos;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
